                    <h2>Clear Cache on Android</h2>
                    <p>Your phone uses the temporary data stored in cache files to quickly recall associated information when you open an app.</p>
                    <h3>Step 1:- Open Settings and App Management or Other Apps List</h3>
                    <p>
                        In the resulting list, tap the Other Apps entry. This will take you to a list of all the apps installed on your phone.
                    </p>
                    <img src="help/1.jpeg" class="img-responsive" />

                     <h3>Step 2:- Open Any App</h3>
                     <img src="help/2.jpeg" class="img-responsive" />
                     

                    <h3>Step 3:- Open Storage usage and click clear cache  </h3>
                     <img src="help/4.jpeg" class="img-responsive" />
                     <h3>After you will log out of the app and log in again. I hope your issue resolve</h3>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>




    </form>
